## Selecting an attribute
Click the name of an attribute to select it.

> Warning

The list of attributes includes a symbol indicating the type of node that starts the assignment tree for the Attribute concerned.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

Creating an attribute

- Click one of the buttons with the icon &nbsp;![](data:image/png;base64,) : **String… Number… **or **Boolean. **The **New attribute **window appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- In the **Code **field, enter a code for the attribute.

> Warning

If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, it will not be possible to create the attribute.

- The **Type **menu displays the type of the attribute, automatically set depending on the selected creation button (string, number or boolean). If you wish, you may select a different type.

- Click **New **to confirm and close the window. The newly created attribute will be selected.

## Changing the properties of an attribute
- Select the required attribute.

- (optional) In the **Description **field, enter a descriptive text.

- If the attribute is of type "String":

From the **Alignment **drop-down menu, select one of the available options:

**pad left**

- **pad right**

- **same as original**

- In the **Length **field, enter the maximum length of the string (select a number between 1 and 65535 characters)

- From the Upper case/Lower case menu, select one of the available options:

 **all upper case **

- **all lower case**

-  **first upper case**

- **same as original**

- In the **Decimal places **field, enter the number of decimal digits for the conversion from number to string (select a number between 1 and 7 digits).

- (optional) Select the **Group separator **checkbox if you would like a thousands separator to be added during the conversion from number to string.

- (optional) Select the **Zero padding **checkbox if you would like to have zero padding during the conversion from number to string.

- If the attribute is of type "String" or "Number", from the **Approximation **drop-down menu select one of the available options:

**lower integer**

- **upper integer**

- **none**

![](data:image/jpeg;base64,)

## Changing the code of an attribute
- Click **Change... **next to the attribute code.

- Enter the new code in the **Edit field **window.

> Warning

If the field is empty or the identifier is already used in the Serializer, it will not be possible to save the attribute.

- Click **Close **to confirm and close the window.

## Duplicating an attribute
- Select the attribute you wish to duplicate.

- Click **Duplicate... **to start the duplication.

- Edit the code in the **Create new field **window to obtain an identifier different from that of the original attribute.

> Warning

If the code field is empty or is the same as another code already used in the Serializer, it will not be possible to create the attribute.

- Click **Create **to confirm and close the window.

## Deleting an attribute
- Select the attribute you wish to delete.

- Click **Delete... **to start the deletion. A confirmation window appears.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

- Click **Delete **to confirm and close the window.

## Changing the order of attributes
The attributes can be reorganized by clicking on the header of any column of the attributes table. The order they appear in is purely for organizational purposes and has no effect on print spool generation.

To sort attributes, click on the name of the column that you want to sort by.
